<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1040" title="Permanent link to this article">Action time to save Social Security</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>OK folks, it&#8217;s time to act. I believe we need to preserve Social Security. It is inherently sound and can be rejuvenated with a few sensible adjustments.</p>

	<p>The &#8220;death&#8221; of Social Security is just another lie from the Bush administration not unlike the weapons of mass destruction in Iraq (please note: <a href="http://www.iht.com/articles/2005/01/13/news/arms.html">they quit looking for them</a>).</p>

	<p>Here&#8217;s what you can do. Send your congressman and Senators an email or letter. Heck, even if you are in favor of this scheme, write a letter, it&#8217;s a good exercise in flexing your power as a citizen and I highly encourage it.</p>

	<p>I did it through MoveOn.org (<a href="http://www.moveon.org/socialsecurity/">here</a>), however you can also easily look up your Senators&#8217; (<a href="http://www.senate.gov/">here</a>) or Rep&#8217;s (<a href="http://www.house.gov/">here</a>) email addresses.</p>

	<p>Go to the extended version to see some basic background information on the topic from MoveOn.org. Also, I copied what I wrote.</p>

	<p>I&#8217;ll tell you what. <b>I have 10 Google email accounts I can give away.</b> The first 10 people who carbon copy me what they wrote to their reps (for or against) will get the still non-public Google email accounts. The kicker is I want them signed (name, city and email) and I will publish them here online. I won&#8217;t publish the email addresses (that&#8217;s how you get the accounts).</p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

<small>This entry was posted on Jan 13 by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a>. You can skip to the end and leave a response using the comment form.</small></p>

</div>

</div>




	

